The interesting thing here is that I've moved away from doing the approach requiring a specialised object, and I believe the reason it is OK to do so is:

The batch will either be in one piece from TransactionStarter or it won't (and therefore will have thrown itself);
If we fail mid-batch, we still unlock all of them - and there is only a single call, so we don't have to handle cases where the closing itself fails midway, because it either fails or succeeds.

